abstract: Google accepts competitive uses of trademarks, prompting some companies to seek legal action.
snippet: Google accepts competitive uses of trademarks, prompting some companies to seek legal action.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  When Audrey Spangenberg idly typed “FirePond,” the name of her small software company, into Google this year, she was not happy with what she saw.

headline.main: Companies Object to Google Policy on Trademarks
headline.print_headline:
Order of Ads
On Google
